parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag may not deploy in a crash
or may deploy improperly
causing injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle uses an excessive amount of oil
requiring frequent refills.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
or deploys improperly
causing injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the windshield can cause visibility issues, leading to accidents or making it difficult to drive safely.
symptoms: The windshield develops a crack
often in an "L" shape
without any apparent impact or reason. The crack can spread rapidly
obscuring the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor quality back-up light can cause a safety hazard, making it difficult to see children or pets behind the vehicle, especially at night.
symptoms: The single back-up light on the lower right side of the bumper is insufficient
causing a blind spot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to weld the roof brace to the frame can weaken the crash resistance in a side impact, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: A rattling noise from the back of the car
which may indicate a loose roof brace.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window motor can cause the window to malfunction, leading to inconvenience and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The window motor wears out
causing the window to stick or not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause shock, injury, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters suddenly
often without warning
and can cause glass to fall into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering light on the dashboard comes on
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
and the power steering warning light remains activated.
